column4: CORRECTED-UPDATE 1-Tesla reports biggest-ever quarterly loss  Model 3 delays
column5: Nov 1 Tesla Inc racked up a $619 million loss in the third quarter  its biggest-ever  driving its shares sharply lower as the electric-car maker spends to speed up production of its more affordable Model 3 sedan.

column4: BRIEF-Tesla posts qtrly net loss per share attributable to stockholders $3.70
column5: * Tesla says about 100 000 Model S and X deliveries projected for 2017
Nov 1 Tesla Inc reported its biggest-ever quarterly loss on Wednesday as the electric-car maker spent more to speed up production of its more affordable Model 3 sedan.

column4: Demand for modem  IoT chips helps Qualcomm top estimates
column5: Qualcomm Inc's fourth-quarter profit and revenue beat market expectations as strength in its smartphone chips business was complemented by demand for chips used in automobiles and for the Internet of Things (IoT).

column4: Qualcomm  JMC seek to exit Alphabet-backed New York WiFi project -sources
column5: SAN FRANCISCO  Nov 1 Chipmaker Qualcomm Inc and private equity firm JMC Capital Partners are looking to sell their stakes in a joint venture that operates more than 1 300 free WiFi kiosks fashioned from old phone booths around New York City  according to people familiar with the matter.
